<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>PottyPlanner</title>
    <link rel="icon" class="favicon" type="image/x-icon" href="/images/logo.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <script src="/js/script.js" defer></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Open+Sans:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Raleway:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="logo">
          <a href="/"><img src="/images/logo.png"></a>
        </div>
        <div class="website-name" >Potty Planner</div>
        <input type="checkbox" id="active">

        <label for="active" class="menu-btn">
            <img src="/images/ham-menu.svg" alt="Menu Icon">
        </label>
        <div class="wrapper">
            <ul>
            <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
            <% if (userId) { %>
                <li><a href="/profiles">Students</a></li>
                <li><a href="/stats">Stats</a></li>
                <li><a href="/feedback">Feedback</a></li>
                <li><a href="/logout">Logout</a></li>
            <% } else { %>
                <li><a href="/login">Login</a></li>
                <li><a href="/register">Register</a></li>
            <% } %>
            </ul>

        </div>

      </header>
    <div class="homepage-visual">
        <div class="parallax-image"></div>
        <h1 class="welcome-text"> Welcome to the Potty Planner App! </h1>
        <a href="/login"> <button class="login-button">Login</button> </a>
        <button class="learn-morebutton" id="learn-more-button">Learn More</button>
        
    </div>

    <div class="Learn-More" id="learn-more-section">
        <div class="homepage-learnmore">
            <h1> Learn More </h1>
        </div>

<div class="box-for-the-table">
<table class="Learn-more-section"> 
    <tr>
        <td>
            <h2 class="header-for-learn-more-section"> What is Potty Planner?</h2>
            <div class="learn-more-info-about-the-website">
                The Potty Planner app is a web-based tool designed to streamline bathroom break management within schools. <br><br>
                Teachers can easily track student bathroom visits by starting and stopping timers with a simple click. <br><br>
                This provides a clear history of each student's bathroom usage, accessible to all staff, allowing for better monitoring and support.
            </div>
        </td>
        <td>
            <h2 class="header-for-learn-more-section"> Why are we doing this?</h2>
            <div class="learn-more-info-about-the-website">
                The Potty Planner app aims to address the challenges of managing bathroom breaks in schools. <br><br>
                By providing a user-friendly interface for teachers, it helps ensure that students' needs are met efficiently and effectively. <br><br>
                The app promotes transparency and communication among staff, enhancing the overall school environment.
        </td>
        <td>
            <h2 class="header-for-learn-more-section"> How does it work?</h2>
            <div class="learn-more-info-about-the-website">
                The Potty Planner app allows teachers to start and stop timers for each student's bathroom visits. <br><br>
                When a student needs to use the bathroom, the teacher clicks "Start" to begin tracking the visit. <br><br>
                Once the student returns, the teacher clicks "Stop," and the visit is logged in the system. <br><br>
                This creates a clear history of each student's bathroom usage, accessible to all staff.
            </div>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>